cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper proposes a novel procedure to add content-addressability to generative models, specifically GANs, without requiring retraining. The paper focuses on image generation problems and presents experiments on various datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves techniques from kernel methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. The paper also involves neural networks, which are a type of computational model used in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves experiments on high-dimensional image generation problems, which could be considered as a sub-topic of cs.SD (Software Development).
